    "term": "Chai tea",
    "letter": "C",
    "definition": "(chi tee) – Chai is the word used for tea in many parts of the world. It is a fragrant milk tea that is growing more popular in the U.S. The tea originated in India, where those in the cooler regions add spices to their tea (not only for flavoring but to induce heat in the body). It is a centuries-old beverage, which has played an important role in many cultures. It is generally made up of rich black tea, milk, a combination of various spices, and a sweetener. The spices used vary from region to region. The most common are cardamom, cinnamon, ginger, cloves, and pepper. It ca n be served following a meal or anytime. Though some Americans serve Chai tea chilled or even iced, Bengal custom is to serve Chai tea hot. Check out Linda’s recipe for Chai Tea – Masala Chai – Spiced Milk Tea."
