    "term": "champignon",
    "letter": "C",
    "definition": "(sham-pee-NYOHN) – French word for an edible mushroom.\n- History:\nIn Greece, around 400 B.C. Hippocrates makes mention of the delicacy of mushrooms that were consumed by the wealthy. The mushroom was thought to possess divine and magical powers. The first written reference to eating mushrooms is the death of a mother and her three children from mushroom poisoning in about 450 B.C. In ancient Rome, the easiest way to get rid of an enemy was to invite him to a disguised mushroom meal using the deadly mushroom from the Borgia family."
